definition.value: A 2-[(4-amino-3,5-dichloro-6-fluoropyridin-2-yl)oxy]propanoic acid that has (R)-configuration. It is a herbicide developed by KingAgroot (an agricultural biotechnology company in China) for the treatment of grass weeds and broadleaf weeds.
A member of the class of aminopyridines that is pyridine substituted by 1-carboxyethoxy, chloro, amino, chloro, and fluoro groups at positions 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6, respectively.
A tetrahydrofuran-2-ylmethyl 2-[(4-amino-3,5-dichloro-6-fluoropyridin-2-yl)oxy]propanoate that has (R)-configuration. It is the proherbicde of fluchloraminopyr.
Conjugate acid of psilocin; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the phosphate group of aeruginascin; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of norlichexanthone; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of griseophenone D; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of griseophenone C; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of griseophenone B; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
